description:
When God was the sovereign, supreme leader, how did He intervene against the enemies of His people? What can we learn about end-time prophecy from the typology of Deborah in the Bible? What does Judges 4 teach about Gods intervention in the final conflict?

The story of Deborah has a particular application to the time in which were living and depicts an eschatological war where God directly intervened to destroy the enemy. Its a type of what will happen at the end of time. Learn what the typology of the story of Deborah can teach us about the leadership of Gods remnant.
